Plain Markdown supports common formatting through a CommonMark-compatible renderer.

### Supported forms

- Headings, paragraphs, emphasis, bold
- Links, ordered and unordered lists, nested lists
- Inline code and fenced code blocks
- Tables, task lists, strikethrough, footnotes
- Raw HTML is preserved

### One clear limitation

Beanstalk template syntax is not interpreted. Dollar-prefixed directives are just text. Bracket-delimited template bodies are just text. Use Beandown if you need Beanstalk-aware content.

### Remember

- The renderer is CommonMark-compatible with GFM extensions.
- It is not the same as Beandown's md renderer.
- Smart punctuation is disabled.